The paper deals with the problem of automatically detecting synapses between neurons in electron microscopy data sets. This involves the use of deep learning algorithms for segmentation and detection, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) research. The paper also introduces novel metrics for evaluating the performance of the algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the processing of large amounts of data, which could also fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) due to the use of natural language processing techniques for data analysis.
